17:
Do you have any idea how much
trouble you caused? A ship—an
extremely valuable asset—gone! On
top of the surprise attack from
hostiles!
24:
Yes. Not a single person was
harmed. It seems it was a feint to
ensure that that Capella woman
escaped.
29:
The worst part was covering it
up—or rather, dealing with the
aftermath. A LOT of hush money is
going to be needed to keep this
quiet.
33:
This is what happens when you
don't follow the rules.
37:
Moving on to our next issue, I ran
into some information about
Capella that's very puzzling. Take a
look at this.
42:
Maiko Warren. Thirty-two years old.
She's... a professional PC gamer?
48:
Yes. She wasn't a biomechanics
scientist until half a year ago.
51:
Her parents are obsessed with
keeping meticulous logs, so we have
a complete record of all her
activities up until half a year ago.
53:
She truly was just a normal person.
It's almost unfathomable that she
somehow possessed knowledge on
dragons from another world.
58:
...Is it possible that an imposter took
her place?
62:
The biological tissue we found in the
lab belonged, without a doubt, to
Maiko Warren.
66:
What if Rooma was a cryptic
artifact? And... what if he wasn't the
only one?
69:
Based on what Keira reported to me,
Capella wore some very distinctive
jewelry.
74: She had a very pretty necklace on.
78:
You've already had experience with
other artifacts capable of
controlling their host—like that
talking armor or objects containing
lingering emotions.
81:
It's possible that Maiko Warren was
being controlled by the Grand
Creator through a cryptic artifact.
91:
I guess we're having red soup with
pumpkins today.
104: Tch, make a break for it!
107: Are you hurt? I can help you.
110: Agh... S-sorry, I can't really move—
119:
Hahaha, how unfortunate that my
little performance was all for naught.
121:
You saw through it, even though this
body's gender, voice, and
personality are different from Maiko...
125: Why did you try to use Armadeus?
128:
You said you cared about him. Liked
him.
131:
So then why did you treat him like
that?
134:
What a fascinating question. You
know, it's a funny thing to use a
different brain to think with. Your
thoughts tend to run differently...
136:
I suppose if I had to say a reason, it
was to make his wish come true.
Completing the curse was his
greatest desire.
141: Rooma had his own wish, you know.
144: How about a little test, then?
146:
The curse of the sword and
dragons—everything was born from
the desire to kill you.
151:
The only one kicking the bucket
today is you, asshole.
168:
You're one of THOSE people, right?
Sorry, but I can see through your
tricks.
172: O Light that reveals all creation!
175:
Pierce the darkness and bring
justice to those deserving!
182:
Oh, how I despise that name.
Wisdom is not in creation, but in
accumulating and assembling
knowledge...
183:
Unfortunately, I see this vessel has
no more to gain. I shall accept this
defeat.
189:
Time to abandon ship... I have no
intention of going down with this
vessel!
192:
He's only unconscious... What did he
do?
198:
He has no memories of the past ten
years?
201:
Keira is still interrogating him, but
the captain and I judged that he
wasn't lying.
203:
The only clue we have now is this
broken bracelet we found on his
wrist.
208:
...Capella wore the exact same one
back in the lab.
212:
So whoever this Grand Creator is,
their real body is always somewhere
else. What a troublesome foe...
214:
I'll be returning to my investigation.
For the time being, refrain from
acting alone and stay vigilant.
219:
Stella, we're your allies. Don't forget
that.
223:
How does dinner sound right about
now? I made pumpkin in tomato
soup.
